sp.p:
Nay, then thou wilt starve, sure;
for here's nothing to be got now-a-days,
unless thou canst fish for't.

sp.l:
I pray ye, greet them fairly. The Gentlemen and the two Sailors descend, and go on board the barge.
Enter, from thence, LYSIMACHUS and Lords;
with the Gentlemen and the two Sailors.
